{"type":"message","id":"aa6b4287","parentId":"f205f169","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:51:36.887Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ktgdwmn2vcdd_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5047\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2285\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation proposed] a\r\n[master 2410c9b] pulse: 2026-03-24 145114\n 6 files changed, 364 insertions(+), 122 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 145114.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 145114.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 145016.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 145114 - The CFI compression experiment identified that binary thresholds fail due to \"constant format\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0). The next step is clearly defined: implement and test the hybrid scoring formula score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) against existing pulse data.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"clear-slug","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5047\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2285\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation proposed] a\r\n[master 2410c9b] pulse: 2026-03-24 145114\n 6 files changed, 364 insertions(+), 122 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 145114.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 145114.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 145016.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 145114 - The CFI compression experiment identified that binary thresholds fail due to \"constant format\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0). The next step is clearly defined: implement and test the hybrid scoring formula score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) against existing pulse data.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378296885}}
{"type":"message","id":"3c520bf8","parentId":"aa6b4287","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:51:36.890Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ktgdwmn2vcdd_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 145016\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on the best action.\r\n\r\nFrom the context:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. There's been extensive work on CFI compression\r\n3. The next pending action is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n4. The formula is: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n5. This needs to distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\r\nLooking at the recent work, there's a synthesis document at `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` that analyzed the 200-pulse experiment.\r\n\r\nThe immediate next step should be:\r\n- Run the hybrid scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n- Compare: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) against binary thresholds\r\n- This requires modifying the pulse script or creating a new analysis script\r\n\r\nSince I'm Breakaway (stateless), I should advance the goals. The most concrete next action is to:\r\n1. Create or update the experiment code for the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Run the analysis\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available. The CFI compression synthesis document likely has the raw data. I need to:\r\n1. Run the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n2. Compare results against the binary threshold approach\r\n\r\nA concrete action would be to create a Python script or PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Calculates hybrid scores using the formula\r\n3. Evaluates precision/recall against ground truth\r\n4. Compares to binary thresholds\r\n\r\nLet me check if there's existing analysis code or if I need to create it. The CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md likely has the methodology.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the goals more carefully:\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll create a targeted script to validate the hybrid scoring approach. The script will process existing pulse data, applying the new formula and comparing performance metrics. This precise experimental setup will help determine if the hybrid scoring method improves over binary thresholds, addressing the key research question about token classification strategy.\r\n\r\nThe experimental design focuses on differentiating between constant format and research trajectory tokens by using a nuanced scoring mechanism that combines CFI and frequency information. By implementing this specific evaluation, I can systematically test the proposed scoring strategy's effectiveness.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) is the next concrete step to advance Phase 1 compression research. The formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` should differentiate \"constant format\" tokens (high freq, high CFI) from \"research trajectory\" tokens (moderate freq, high CFI), but this needs empirical validation against the existing 200-pulse dataset.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate Python analysis script to run Strategy C hybrid scoring experiment and compare against binary threshold results from the prior experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```python\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: \"\"\"\r\nCFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C\r\nTests: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\nAgainst: Binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n\"\"\"\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\n# Load pulse data\r\npulses_dir = Path(\"pulses\")\r\npulse_files = sorted(pulses_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))[:200]\r\n\r\n# Collect token stats across all pulses\r\ntoken_stats = {}  # token -> {\"freq\": int, \"cfi\": float, \"pulses\": [ids]}\r\nfor pfile in pulse_files:\r\n    pid = pfile.stem\r\n    content = pfile.read_text()\r\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\r\n        if '|' in line and not line.startswith('|'):\r\n            parts = line.split('|')\r\n            if len(parts) >= 4:\r\n                token = parts[2].strip()\r\n                if token:\r\n                    if token not in token_stats:\r\n                        token_stats[token] = {\"freq\": 0, \"pulses\": []}\r\n                    token_stats[token][\"freq\"] += 1\r\n                    token_stats[token][\"pulses\"].append(pid)\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI: fraction of pulses where token appears at predicted position\r\n# For simplicity, use frequency-based CFI estimate\r\nfor token, stats in token_stats.items():\r\n    stats[\"cfi\"] = 1.0  # Placeholder - would need actual position tracking\r\n\r\n# Load ground truth labels (if available) or use heuristic\r\n# Ground truth = research-significant tokens\r\n# Heuristic: tokens appearing in Phase-related content\r\n\r\n# Strategy C: Hybrid scoring\r\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\r\n    return cfi * min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\r\n\r\n# Strategy B (baseline): Binary threshold\r\ndef binary_threshold(cfi, freq, cfi_thresh=0.7, freq_min=3, freq_max=120):\r\n    return cfi >= cfi_thresh and freq_min <= freq < freq_max\r\n\r\n# Compute scores for all tokens\r\nresults = []\r\nfor token, stats in token_stats.items():\r\n    cfi = stats[\"cfi\"]\r\n    freq = stats[\"freq\"]\r\n    h_score = hybrid_score(cfi, freq)\r\n    binary = binary_threshold(cfi, freq)\r\n    results.append({\r\n        \"token\": token,\r\n        \"freq\": freq,\r\n        \"cfi\": cfi,\r\n        \"hybrid_score\": h_score,\r\n        \"binary_pass\": binary\r\n    })\r\n\r\n# Sort by hybrid score\r\nresults.sort(key=lambda x: x[\"hybrid_score\"], reverse=True)\r\n\r\n# Output top tokens by hybrid score\r\nprint(\"=== Top 20 Tokens by Hybrid Score ===\")\r\nprint(f\"{'Token':\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:50:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378296887}}
